Duboc:
I'm scared, I'm scared.
Oh my God, oh my God.

23:35.934 --> 23:37.642
I'm gonna be sick.
I'm gonna throw up.

23:39.809 --> 23:41.558
So, you should feel the effects
about an hour or two.

23:41.642 --> 23:42.892
And what should I feel?

23:42.976 --> 23:44.684
Energy, mental clarity.

23:44.767 --> 23:47.267
Why aren't doctors
prescribing this

23:47.350 --> 23:49.558
in a more mainstream
medical sense?

23:49.642 --> 23:51.892
When you're in medical school,
no one talks about
vitamin therapy.

23:51.976 --> 23:53.892
It's not taught
in the curriculum.

23:53.976 --> 23:55.600
Everyone talks
about antibiotics,

23:55.684 --> 23:57.267
and trying to cure
disease through

23:57.350 --> 23:58.767
antibiotics,
not through vitamins.

23:58.850 --> 24:00.725
-Thank you so much.
-Yeah, thank you for coming by.

24:00.809 --> 24:02.267
I'm sorry I was such a baby!

24:02.350 --> 24:04.101
-No, you were great.

24:04.184 --> 24:06.433
Duboc:
Many attendees
find inspiration

24:06.517 --> 24:08.976
in Goop's message that
more conventional medicine

24:09.059 --> 24:10.600
isn't your only option.

24:10.684 --> 24:14.059
For me, personally,
Western medicine failed me.

24:14.142 --> 24:15.892
In one appointment,
he was like,

24:15.976 --> 24:18.308
"Oh, you have this.
Here's this prescription."

24:18.392 --> 24:20.934
And tried to send me
on my way. I was like, no!

24:21.017 --> 24:22.976
I know there's something
deeper going on,

24:23.059 --> 24:25.059
and I know it's not
just this one thing

24:25.142 --> 24:27.267
that you labeled me under,
which is so common,

24:27.350 --> 24:29.433
which is IBS. I'm like,

24:29.517 --> 24:32.600
I'm sorry, but that's BS
because no.

24:32.684 --> 24:36.433
And it ended up being
leaky gut, and Hashimoto's,
and I lost my period.

24:36.517 --> 24:38.350
So, that's why I've turned
to functional medicine

24:38.433 --> 24:40.433
because it's helped
me so much more.

24:40.517 --> 24:43.976
Duboc:
But for all the faith Goop
devotees have in the brand,

24:44.059 --> 24:46.101
it is has been a target
of harsh criticism

24:46.184 --> 24:48.475
for the promotion
of certain products.

24:48.558 --> 24:50.809
The non-profit organization,
Truth in Advertising,

24:50.892 --> 24:53.767
filed a complaint with several
California district attorneys,

24:53.850 --> 24:56.475
alleging Goop made 51
deceptive health claims

24:56.558 --> 24:58.226
about the products it promote.

24:58.892 --> 25:00.809
We wanted to ask
Goop about the ethics

25:00.892 --> 25:03.350
of playing health guru
to thousands of women.

25:03.433 --> 25:06.142
So, we went straight to
Gwyneth Paltrow herself.

25:06.226 --> 25:07.267
-Hi!
-Thank you.

25:07.350 --> 25:08.350
I know you're tired.

25:08.433 --> 25:10.184
I've had my
B-12 shot, so...

25:10.267 --> 25:12.642
So did I, and it's
fucking not working.

25:14.059 --> 25:16.267
So, we're here at
the Goop Summit,

25:16.350 --> 25:18.934
and wellness is booming.

25:20.558 --> 25:24.059
What do you think it has to
say about society in America?

25:24.142 --> 25:25.684
Well, I think that

25:25.767 --> 25:27.142
the idea of wellness
really starts

25:27.226 --> 25:28.850
to resonate
with people when

25:28.934 --> 25:31.809
either they, or someone
that they love very much,

25:31.892 --> 25:34.142
is in some kind of
a health crisis,

25:34.226 --> 25:38.017
and the answers
are not effective.

25:38.101 --> 25:41.017
-Mm-hmm.
-It's not about throwing
out Western medicine,

25:41.101 --> 25:42.350
but it really is

25:42.433 --> 25:44.350
about understanding
that the consumer,

25:44.433 --> 25:47.226
especially women in America
who aren't feeling well,

25:47.308 --> 25:48.892
and who are feeling unheard,

25:48.976 --> 25:50.725
people really want now

25:50.809 --> 25:53.142
to have autonomy in
their wellness journey,

25:53.226 --> 25:54.892
and so the consumer
is starting

25:54.976 --> 25:57.184
to shape the way all
of this is happening.

25:57.267 --> 25:58.892
Yeah, we've been
hearing that all day.

25:58.976 --> 26:02.350
Women are finding
themselves feeling dismissed

26:02.433 --> 26:05.433
by conventional routes.
They want more options.

26:05.517 --> 26:08.059
But, I mean,
here you do offer

26:08.142 --> 26:10.892
products and practices
that are

26:10.976 --> 26:13.350
accepted by
the medical consensus

26:13.433 --> 26:16.101
-that have peer-reviewed
scientific studies.
-Right.

26:16.184 --> 26:18.059
But then, you offer
things that haven't,

26:18.142 --> 26:19.850
-but they're all
under the same roof.
-Right.

26:19.934 --> 26:21.934
Well, I think,
the idea is that

26:22.017 --> 26:23.226
science is always changing,

26:23.308 --> 26:25.226
and theories are
always changing, and,

26:25.308 --> 26:27.892
of course,
evidence is key.

26:27.976 --> 26:30.517
But, sometimes, evidence
is anecdotal for people.

26:30.600 --> 26:33.184
So, these debates
spark where, you know,

26:33.267 --> 26:35.892
as something is emerging
and as ideas are shifting,

26:35.976 --> 26:38.184
-there's always
a lot of resistance...
-Yeah.

26:38.267 --> 26:40.558
...by the status quo,
and that's okay.

26:40.642 --> 26:42.433
And we're
always saying,

26:42.517 --> 26:43.976
take everything
with a grain of salt.

26:44.059 --> 26:45.934
Take everything your
conventional doctor says

26:46.017 --> 26:47.392
with a grain of salt,
and take everything

26:47.475 --> 26:48.809
your healer's saying
with a grain of salt.

26:48.892 --> 26:50.934
But what's resonant for you?

26:52.558 --> 26:53.558
Okay, fine.

26:53.642 --> 26:55.101
So, lastly,

26:55.184 --> 26:58.059
we're in this kind of terrifying
age of misinformation,

26:58.142 --> 27:01.142
and science itself is,
sort of, under attack.

27:02.184 --> 27:04.433
Why not be
the vanguard and,

27:04.517 --> 27:06.267
you know,
help women

27:06.350 --> 27:08.600
know what is really,
peer-reviewed

27:08.684 --> 27:11.101
and evidence-based science,
and what isn't?

27:11.184 --> 27:12.433
We do!

27:12.517 --> 27:15.767
We tag our contents if
something is evidence-based,

27:15.850 --> 27:18.308
peer-reviewed science,
then it's tagged as such.

27:18.392 --> 27:21.976
And if it's an emerging
modality, we tag it as such.

27:22.059 --> 27:24.059
So, we're very clear
about what is what.

27:24.142 --> 27:26.101
But not in the way that
conventional medicine says,

27:26.184 --> 27:27.725
"this works,
and this doesn't."

27:28.934 --> 27:30.642
-So, so for example,

27:30.725 --> 27:33.184
if something
doesn't work,

27:33.267 --> 27:34.684
you're not saying that.

27:34.767 --> 27:36.600
-Yeah. For example,

27:36.684 --> 27:38.767
meditation,
science says it works,

27:38.850 --> 27:40.809
whereas some of the other
things you offer,

27:40.892 --> 27:42.600
like vitamin pills,

27:42.684 --> 27:46.142
are proven not to work in
the way that Goop says they do.

27:46.226 --> 27:48.392
Well, I think that,
you know,

27:49.226 --> 27:50.767
for example, with vitamins,

27:50.850 --> 27:52.850
if you are deficient
in a vitamin,

27:52.934 --> 27:54.475
then a supplement
really does work,

27:54.558 --> 27:57.184
and there's a lot
of data behind that.

27:57.267 --> 27:59.142
But, apparently,
we're not deficient--

28:01.433 --> 28:04.517
Okay. All right. Fine.
Thank you so much.

28:04.600 --> 28:06.976
-We've had an amazing time.
Thank you.
-Good!

