28:18.892 --> 28:21.142
for, "misrepresentations about

28:21.226 --> 28:23.392
the effects, efficacy,
or attributes"

28:23.475 --> 28:24.892
of some of their products,

28:24.976 --> 28:28.059
including their
infamous vagina eggs.

28:28.142 --> 28:29.684
Goop released
a statement calling it,

28:29.767 --> 28:31.350
an "honest disagreement,"

28:31.433 --> 28:33.809
thanking the task force
for its, "guidance,"

28:33.892 --> 28:36.475
as the brand moves from
a "pioneer in this space

28:36.558 --> 28:39.017
to an established
wellness authority."

28:39.101 --> 28:42.475
Goop denies liability,
and is still selling
the eggs.

28:42.558 --> 28:43.892
All it did was reword

28:43.976 --> 28:46.517
the product description
on the website.

28:46.600 --> 28:48.392
With limited
government oversight,

28:48.475 --> 28:50.433
Goop's and other
companies' products

28:50.517 --> 28:54.392
are left to be regulated
by consumer complaints
and the marketplace.

28:54.475 --> 28:57.059
And celebrities
and social media influencers

28:57.142 --> 28:58.892
continue to be
the driving force

28:58.976 --> 29:00.684
behind the wellness industry,

29:00.767 --> 29:02.433
even when the products
and health claims

29:02.517 --> 29:04.517
they make are called
into question.

